2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving the scan alignment problem, which can be useful in robotics applications. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with 3D modeling and alignment, which is a common topic in computer graphics. 
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper proposes a new method for solving the registration problem based on line intersection constraints, which is a common topic in computational geometry. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with 3D scan alignment, which is a common topic in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality.
